Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of twenty (20) years.  Ten (10) years initial confinement, followed by ten (10) years extended supervision.  Execution of sentence is stayed and defendant is placed on probation for five (5) years.  Conditions of probation are:
1) Spend twelve (12) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, to commence on 01-15-16 at 5:00 p.m.;
2) Maintain absolute sobriety;
3) Have no unsupervised contact with anyone under the age of 18, except for his own children with the approval of the agent;
4) Complete psycho-sex evaluation and comply with recommendations;
5) Maintain full-time employment/job search;
6) Have no contact with the victim or her family; 
7) If during probation the child loses her insurance, defendant will be responsible for the payment of her counseling and medications;
8) Register as sex offender and comply with sex offender registry;
9) Pay costs of action; 
10) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
11) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
12) Submit DNA sample;
13) Defendant is not to possess or own any internet enabled device without the agent's approval.  
Court finds defendant is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.   
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief. 
Voter Ineligibility Notice and Acknowledgment. 
